summary: This is an administrative response from the FBI New York office to the New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services regarding a fingerprint search request. It indicates that records can be obtained through the Interstate Identification Index using the appropriate NCIC transaction.

keyFacts: The document is an FBI administrative response dated October 6, 2021, regarding a fingerprint search request.
The request was made by the New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services, with Michael C. Green listed as Executive Deputy Commissioner.
The response indicates that the requested record(s) can be obtained through the Interstate Identification Index (III) using the appropriate NCIC transaction.
The document is part of the Epstein case files, suggesting a law enforcement inquiry related to the investigation.
The response is labeled as a 'Stale Delayed Response Additional Inquiry Response,' indicating it may be a follow-up to a prior request.
